System (10) was solved numerically by truncating it and using the iteration method of successive approximations. Integration was done using the mid-rectangles method realized by dividing the finite time interval [0,T] being investigated into equal segments of length Δτ. System functions Amn and p were approximated with piecewise constant analogs Amn and p  (Amn, p ∈ RT/Δτ) in the domain of variation of variable τ:
Amn(τ)=∑i=1T/Δτ(Amn)i·[H(τ-τi-1)-H(τ-τi)];p(τ)=∑i=1T/Δτpi·[H(τ-τi-1)-H(τ-τi)];
where τi=i·Δτ are dissection nodes.
